.\" ------------------------------------------------------------------
.TH mbimapidle 1 "@DATE@" "mbimapidle (@VERSION@)" "User Commands"

.SH NAME
mbimapidle \- execute command on new IMAP messages
.SH SYNOPSIS

\fBmbimapidle\fR [\fIoptions\fR]
.br
.

.SH DESCRIPTION
.P
\fBmbimapidle\fR maintains persistent server connection using IMAP protocol (RFC
2177) IDLE extension and execute sync command on new messages.
.

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.TP
\fB-h\fR, \fB--help\fR
Display a summary of command line options.
.TP
\fB-v\fR, \fB--version\fR
Display version information.
.TP
\fB-d\fR, \fB--debug\fR
Print debugging messages (default: disabled)
.TP
\fB-f\fR, \fB--foreground\fR
Run in the foreground instead of forking into a background process (default:
run the background)
.

.SH "CONFIGURATION"
The configuration file is mandatory and should be located at
.TP
\fB$XDG_CONFIG_HOME/mbimapidle/mbimapidlerc\fR (usually \fB~/.config/mbimapidle/mbimapidlerc\fR)
.TP
.P
Lines starting with (#) are comments and are ignored. Configuration file is
defined in sections, an optional [general] section and [MailBoxName] section
defining a mailbox to monitor, you can add as much [MailBoxName] as you like.
.
.SS General section [general]
This is an optional section currently controls only daemon verbosity
.TP
\fBverbose\fR=\fI"value"\fR 
set value to \fBtrue\fR to enabled verbosity, default value \fBfalse\fR.  Note
if verbosity is set to \fBfalse\fR, and \fBmbimapidle\fR is run with \fB-d\fR,
\fB--debug\fR you will still get verbose messages.
.SS Mail box section [MailBoxName]

For a sample configuration file, please checkout out:
.TP
\fB@CONF_EXAMPLE@\fR
.

.SH AUTHOR
Ali Abdallah (ali.abdallah@suse.com)
